OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F371A1784558904
OL,3,CNew museum in country house reveals
OL,4,Csecrets of espionage during WWII
OL,6,FTrent Park House of Secrets is a new
OL,7,Fmuseum in a historic country house in
OL,8,FEnfield, north London, which tells the
OL,9,Fstories of its former owner and
OL,10,Fespionage during World War Two.
OL,12,FThe museum - which as been restored to
OL,13,Fits 1930's appearance on the inside -
OL,14,Fbrings together both parts of the
OL,15,Fbuilding's history.
OL,17,FThe state rooms on the ground floor
OL,18,Freflect the lavish lifestyle of its
OL,19,Fprevious owner - Sir Philip Sassoon -
OL,20,Fand senior German officers who were
OL,21,Fheld captive there during the war.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G1/12
