FL,372,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37102
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F371A1784558904
OL,3,CNew museum in country house reveals
OL,4,Csecrets of espionage during WWII
OL,6,FIn the basement, visitors can see the
OL,7,Flistening stations, offices and
OL,8,Fworking rooms of the Secret Listeners
OL,9,Fwho collected vital intelligence.
OL,11,FHow Trent Park House became a secret
OL,12,Flistening house
OL,14,FTrent Park is the former residence of
OL,15,FSir Philip Sassoon, one of the
OL,16,Fwealthiest men in England at the time.
OL,17,FHe inherited it in 1912 from his
OL,18,Ffather, Sir Edward Sassoon.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G2/12
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,372,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37103
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F371A1784558904
OL,3,CNew museum in country house reveals
OL,4,Csecrets of espionage during WWII
OL,6,FPhilip Sassoon was a close friend of
OL,7,Fwar-time leader Winston Churchill and
OL,8,Fserved as an MP and as Under-Secretary
OL,9,Fof State for Air.
OL,11,FThe bachelor would entertain political
OL,12,Ffriends, members of the Royal Family,
OL,13,Fand artists such as Charlie Chaplin
OL,14,Fand Fred Astaire on weekends.
OL,16,FSassoon died of the flu in 1939 and
OL,17,Fthe house was requisitioned by the
OL,18,Fgovernment as a centre for
OL,19,Fintelligence operations.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G3/12
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,372,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37104
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F371A1784558904
OL,3,CNew museum in country house reveals
OL,4,Csecrets of espionage during WWII
OL,6,FBetween 1939 and the end of the Second
OL,7,FWorld War, the house was used as a
OL,8,Fprison for senior German officers.
OL,10,FWhile prisoners thought they were
OL,11,Fbeing treated like upper-class
OL,12,Fofficers, they were unaware their
OL,13,Fconversations were being recorded.
OL,15,FVital information was obtained by a
OL,16,Fnetwork of listening devices hidden in
OL,17,Fevery corner of the house.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G4/12
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,372,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37105
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F371A1784558904
OL,3,CNew museum in country house reveals
OL,4,Csecrets of espionage during WWII
OL,6,FListening devices were placed in walls
OL,7,Fand skirtings, light fittings, plant
OL,8,Fpots, window ledges, the billiard
OL,9,Ftable, and even the garden benches.
OL,11,FA network of secret listeners would be
OL,12,Fstationed in the basement of the house
OL,13,Frecording conversations.
OL,15,FThere were roughly 40 secret listeners
OL,16,Fat Trent Park - many being German-
OL,17,Fspeaking Jewish refugees.
OL,19,FThe grandfather of writer and comedian
OL,20,FHelen Lederer was a secret listener -
OL,21,Funknown to her until recently.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G5/12
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,372,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37106
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F371A1784558904
OL,3,CNew museum in country house reveals
OL,4,Csecrets of espionage during WWII
OL,6,FErnst Lederer was recruited by the
OL,7,FIntelligence Corps and posted to Trent
OL,8,FPark after arriving in the UK from
OL,9,FCzechoslovakia in 1939.
OL,11,FHe was rumoured to be tasked with
OL,12,Fmingling with the German generals to
OL,13,Fmanipulate their conversations and
OL,14,Ftease out information.
OL,16,FHelen Lederer said: "The fact that my
OL,17,Fgrandfather was a secret listener was
OL,18,Fa secret he took to the grave.
OL,26,@xD@UOU
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G6/12
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,372,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37107
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F371A1784558904
OL,3,CNew museum in country house reveals
OL,4,Csecrets of espionage during WWII
OL,6,F"It means so much that this chapter of
OL,7,Flittle-known history can be told
OL,8,Fthrough the museum.
OL,10,F"To imagine what the secret listeners
OL,11,Fmay have felt as they listened to the
OL,12,Fcaptive generals upstairs is as
OL,13,Fimportant as it is humbling."
OL,15,FDr Giuseppe Albano, Director ofTrent
OL,16,FPark House of Secrets, said: "Most
OL,17,Fpeople will come to Trent Park to
OL,18,Fdiscover the covert intelligence
OL,19,Foperation that took place here during
OL,20,Fthe Second World War.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G7/12
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,372,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37108
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F371A1784558904
OL,3,CNew museum in country house reveals
OL,4,Csecrets of espionage during WWII
OL,6,F"What I hope will surprise them is
OL,7,Fthat there is so much more to discover.
OL,9,F"Before the war, these rooms played
OL,10,Fhost to conversations between
OL,11,Fpoliticians, royalty, writers and
OL,12,Fartists at a moment when Europe stood
OL,13,Fon the brink of conflict.
OL,15,F"We have taken great care to reveal
OL,16,Fthe full significance of the house,
OL,17,Fweaving together stories from some of
OL,18,Fthe most colourful and turbulent years
OL,19,Fof twentieth-century British history."
OL,21,FSecrets discovered at Trent Park
OL,26,@{D@fO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G8/12
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,372,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37109
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F371A1784558904
OL,3,CNew museum in country house reveals
OL,4,Csecrets of espionage during WWII
OL,6,FThe first scoop of the war came from
OL,7,Fprisoners who had been captured from
OL,8,Fsunken German U-boats.
OL,10,FBritish naval intelligence wanted to
OL,11,Fknow how the German 'Enigma' cipher
OL,12,Fmachines coded instructions to the U-
OL,13,Fboats at sea.
OL,15,FCritical intelligence was gained from
OL,16,Fa conversation between a pilot and a U-
OL,17,Fboat officer, recorded in January 1940.
OL,19,FSecret listeners were able to
OL,20,Funderstand that Bletchley Park was a
OL,21,Fkey in understanding the codes.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G9/12
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,372,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37110
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F371A1784558904
OL,3,CNew museum in country house reveals
OL,4,Csecrets of espionage during WWII
OL,6,FAnother conversation which helped win
OL,7,Fthe war was recorded in early 1941
OL,8,Fbetween two bomber pilots, who
OL,9,Frevealed that on night missions they
OL,10,Fused a system of transmitted
OL,11,Fnavigation beams.
OL,13,FThis enabled them to target British
OL,14,Fmunitions factories accurately.
OL,16,FThe information was then verified by
OL,17,Fintelligence officers at Bletchley
OL,18,FPark using Enigma, and gave Air
OL,19,FIntelligence information to jam the
OL,20,Fsystem.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                G10/12
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,372,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37111
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F371A1784558904
OL,3,CNew museum in country house reveals
OL,4,Csecrets of espionage during WWII
OL,6,FOne of the most significant
OL,7,Fconversations was recorded on 22 March
OL,8,F1943 between two generals.
OL,10,FThey discussed weapons being developed
OL,11,Fby German scientists that could travel
OL,12,F'15km into the stratosphere'.
OL,14,FThe British government realised that
OL,15,Fthe Germans were developing ballistic
OL,16,Frockets, and with further
OL,17,Finterrogation and eavesdropping, more
OL,18,Fevidence came to light about Hitler's
OL,19,Fsecret weapons programme.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                G11/12
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
